 Paul Rudd and Seann William Scott star in Role Models as Danny 
 and Wheeler, two salesmen who trash a company truck on an energy 
 drink-fueled bender. Upon their arrest, the court gives them a 
 choice: do hard time or spend 150 hours with a mentorship program. 
 After one day with the kids, however, jail doesn't look half bad. 
 Once the center's ex-con director (Jane Lynch) gives them an 
 ultimatum, Danny and Wheeler are forced to tailor their brand of 
 immature wisdom to their charges, Augie (Christopher Mintz-Plasse) 
 and Ronnie (Bobb'e J. Thompson). And if they can just make it 
 through probation without getting thrown in jail, the world's 
 worst role models will prove that, sometimes, it takes a village 
 idiot to raise a child.
